The [libexpat](https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat) library implements a stream-oriented XML parser. 

The vulnerability is within an libexpat mechanism that was not configured to track or limit the total amount of memory it could allocate while parsing a document. This made the library susceptible to a class of attacks known as XML bombs, which are designed to exploit the parser's resource consumption.

The vulnerability can be triggered when libexpat parses crafted XML input, for example - 
```
